&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Red Hat offers a cluster based on Open Source solutions. This document explains how to set one up.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Installing a Red Hat 4 Cluster</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Installation_d%5C%27un_cluster_Red_Hat_4/</link><pubDate>Sun, 26 Feb 2012 13:24:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Installation_d%5C%27un_cluster_Red_Hat_4/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;strong>To install Red Hat Enterprise with Cluster Suite, take CDs or DVD and boot from it.&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>We are going to see step by step the interesting components.&lt;/p>
